---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'Terms | Lift and Measure';
const description = 'Terms of use for Lift and Measure, covering accuracy, medical disclaimers, acceptable use, and liability.';
const path = '/terms';
const lastUpdated = 'July 7, 2026';

const schema = {
  '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
  itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://liftandmeasure.com' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Terms', item: 'https://liftandmeasure.com/terms' },
  ],
};
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} path={path} schema={schema}>
  <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a>
    <span class="sep">&gt;</span>
    <span aria-current="page">Terms</span>
  </nav>

  <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
  <p class="disclaimer">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

  <p>
    By using Lift and Measure, you agree to the terms below. If you do not agree with them,
    please do not use the site.
  </p>

  <h2>Use of the Tools</h2>
  <p>
    The calculators on this site are provided for general informational and reference purposes.
    They are free to use, and no account or payment is required.
  </p>

  <h2>Not Medical or Professional Advice</h2>
  <p>
    Nothing on this site is medical, dietary, or professional fitness advice. Calculators such as
    body fat percentage, macro targets, TDEE, and heart rate zones produce formula-based
    estimates, not diagnoses or personalized recommendations. Before making significant changes to
    your diet, training, or exercise intensity, especially if you have an existing health
    condition, are pregnant, or are new to exercise, consult a qualified healthcare provider or
    certified professional.
  </p>

  <h2>Accuracy</h2>
  <p>
    We aim for every formula and reference table on this site to be correct and to use widely
    accepted standard values, such as the Mifflin-St Jeor equation, the US Navy body fat method,
    the Boer lean body mass formula, standard MET values, and the original 1994 Wilks coefficient
    formula. Even so, results are provided "as is" without any guarantee of accuracy for a
    specific purpose, and individual results can vary from formula-based estimates. Do not rely on
    this site as the sole basis for medical, legal, financial, or safety-related decisions. When a
    decision matters, verify important figures independently or consult a qualified professional.
  </p>

  <h2>No Warranty</h2>
  <p>
    This site is provided without warranties of any kind, whether express or implied, including
    warranties of accuracy, reliability, or fitness for a particular purpose.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the fullest extent permitted by law, Lift and Measure is not liable for any loss or damage,
    including any injury arising from exercise undertaken based on information from this site,
    arising from your use of, or inability to use, this site or the information it provides.
  </p>

  <h2>Acceptable Use</h2>
  <p>
    You agree not to misuse the site, including attempting to disrupt its normal operation,
    scraping it at a scale that degrades service for other visitors, or using it for any unlawful
    purpose.
  </p>

  <h2>Advertising</h2>
  <p>
    This site is supported by advertising, including Google AdSense. Ads are clearly labeled and
    separated from the tools and written content on each page. See the
    <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> for details on cookies and data use related to
    advertising.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
  <p>
    These terms may be updated from time to time. Continued use of the site after a change means
    you accept the updated terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these terms can be sent to
    <a href="mailto:contact@liftandmeasure.com">contact@liftandmeasure.com</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
